{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":954,"text":"It is very fashionable and proper \nto speak about food\n"},{"time":8319,"text":"in all its forms, all its colors, \naromas and tastes."},{"time":15529,"text":"But after the food goes through \nthe digestive system,"},{"time":21183,"text":"when it is thrown out as crap,"},{"time":24429,"text":"it is no longer fashionable\nto speak about it."},{"time":28026,"text":"It is rather revolting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33192,"text":"I'm a guy who has graduated \nfrom bullshit to full-shit."},{"time":40732,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":43801,"text":"My organization, Gram Vikas, which means\n\"village development organization,\""},{"time":50466,"text":"was working in the area \nof renewable energy."},{"time":53572,"text":"On the most part, we were \nproducing biogas,"},{"time":57322,"text":"biogas for rural kitchens."},{"time":62257,"text":"We produce biogas in India \nby using animal manure,"},{"time":68147,"text":"which usually, in India, \nis called cow dung."},{"time":70551,"text":"But as the gender-sensitive \nperson that I am,"},{"time":74605,"text":"I would like to call it bullshit."},{"time":77533,"text":"But realizing later on"},{"time":79916,"text":"how important were sanitation\nand the disposal of crap in a proper way,"},{"time":87493,"text":"we went into the arena of sanitation."},{"time":93071,"text":"Eighty percent of all diseases \nin India and most developing countries"},{"time":101870,"text":"are because of poor quality water."},{"time":105917,"text":"And when we look at the reason \nfor poor quality water,"},{"time":109511,"text":"you find that it is our abysmal attitude \nto the disposal of human waste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116305,"text":"Human waste, in its rawest form,"},{"time":120344,"text":"finds its way back to drinking water,\nbathing water, washing water,"},{"time":126400,"text":"irrigation water, whatever water you see."},{"time":130293,"text":"And this is the cause for 80 percent \nof the diseases in rural areas."},{"time":137474,"text":"In India, it is unfortunately only the\nwomen who carry water."},{"time":143695,"text":"So for all domestic needs,\nwomen have to carry water."},{"time":148824,"text":"So that is a pitiable state of affairs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154178,"text":"Open defecation is rampant."},{"time":156761,"text":"Seventy percent of India\ndefecates in the open."},{"time":161713,"text":"They sit there out in the open,"},{"time":164150,"text":"with the wind on their sails,"},{"time":166178,"text":"hiding their faces, exposing their bases,"},{"time":170021,"text":"and sitting there in pristine glory --"},{"time":174889,"text":"70 percent of India."},{"time":177195,"text":"And if you look at the world total,"},{"time":180428,"text":"60 percent of all the crap that is thrown\ninto the open is by Indians."},{"time":189153,"text":"A fantastic distinction."},{"time":191929,"text":"I don't know if we Indians can be proud\nof such a distinction."},{"time":196081,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":198096,"text":"So we, together with a lot of villages,"},{"time":200278,"text":"we began to talk about how to really \naddress this situation of sanitation."},{"time":205022,"text":"And we came together and formed \na project called MANTRA."},{"time":210979,"text":"MANTRA stands for Movement and Action\nNetwork for Transformation of Rural Areas."},{"time":218256,"text":"So we are speaking about transformation,\ntransformation in rural areas."},{"time":225612,"text":"Villages that agree \nto implement this project,"},{"time":229224,"text":"they organize a legal society"},{"time":232087,"text":"where the general body \nconsists of all members"},{"time":236453,"text":"who elect a group of men and women\nwho implement the project"},{"time":242336,"text":"and, later on, who look after\nthe operation and maintenance."},{"time":247101,"text":"They decide to build a toilet \nand a shower room."},{"time":252862,"text":"And from a protected water source,"},{"time":255943,"text":"water will be brought to an elevated water\nreservoir and piped to all households"},{"time":262862,"text":"through three taps:"},{"time":265327,"text":"one in the toilet, one in the shower, \none in the kitchen, 24 hours a day."},{"time":272769,"text":"The pity is that our cities,\nlike New Delhi and Bombay,"},{"time":276940,"text":"do not have a 24-hour water supply."},{"time":280371,"text":"But in these villages, we want to have it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285084,"text":"There is a distinct difference \nin the quality."},{"time":289459,"text":"Well in India, we have a theory,\nwhich is very much accepted"},{"time":295328,"text":"by the government bureaucracy\nand all those who matter,"},{"time":298910,"text":"that poor people deserve poor solutions"},{"time":303823,"text":"and absolutely poor people deserve\npathetic solutions."},{"time":310058,"text":"This, combined with \na Nobel Prize-worthy theory that"},{"time":316503,"text":"the cheapest is the most economic,"},{"time":318872,"text":"is the heady cocktail that the poor\nare forced to drink."},{"time":326091,"text":"We are fighting against this."},{"time":328450,"text":"We feel that the poor have been\nhumiliated for centuries."},{"time":334941,"text":"And even in sanitation,"},{"time":337359,"text":"they should not be humiliated."},{"time":339545,"text":"Sanitation is more about dignity"},{"time":342239,"text":"than about human disposal of waste."},{"time":344907,"text":"And so you build these toilets \nand very often,"},{"time":349236,"text":"we have to hear that the toilets are\nbetter than their houses."},{"time":355442,"text":"And you can see that in front are \nthe attached houses"},{"time":359323,"text":"and the others are the toilets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362151,"text":"So these people, without a single\nexception of a family in a village,"},{"time":368799,"text":"decide to build a toilet, a bathing room."},{"time":372598,"text":"And for that, they come together,\ncollect all the local materials --"},{"time":378256,"text":"local materials like rubble, \nsand, aggregates,"},{"time":383611,"text":"usually a government subsidy is available"},{"time":386139,"text":"to meet at least part of the cost \nof external materials"},{"time":389417,"text":"like cement, steel, toilet commode."},{"time":394211,"text":"And they build a toilet \nand a bathing room."},{"time":398317,"text":"Also, all the unskilled laborers, that is \ndaily wage earners, mostly landless,"},{"time":404695,"text":"are given an opportunity to be \ntrained as masons and plumbers."},{"time":412098,"text":"So while these people are being trained, \nothers are collecting the materials."},{"time":417175,"text":"And when both are ready,\nthey build a toilet, a shower room,"},{"time":422841,"text":"and of course also a water tower, \nan elevated water reservoir."},{"time":429840,"text":"We use a system of two leach pits \nto treat the waste."},{"time":435171,"text":"From the toilet, the muck comes\ninto the first leach pit."},{"time":439469,"text":"And when it is full, it is blocked \nand it can go to the next."},{"time":444494,"text":"But we discovered that if you plant\nbanana trees, papaya trees"},{"time":449343,"text":"on the periphery of these leach pits,"},{"time":452726,"text":"they grow very well\nbecause they suck up all the nutrients"},{"time":455987,"text":"and you get very tasty bananas, papayas."},{"time":461478,"text":"If any of you come to my place,"},{"time":464180,"text":"I would be happy to share\nthese bananas and papayas with you."},{"time":469478,"text":"So there you can see \nthe completed toilets, the water towers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475288,"text":"This is in a village where \nmost of the people are even illiterate."},{"time":481098,"text":"It is always a 24-hour water supply"},{"time":483508,"text":"because water gets polluted\nvery often when you store it --"},{"time":489114,"text":"a child dips his or her hand into it,\nsomething falls into it."},{"time":494936,"text":"So no water is stored. It's always on tap."},{"time":501288,"text":"This is how an elevated \nwater reservoir is constructed."},{"time":505416,"text":"And that is the end product."},{"time":507596,"text":"Because it has to go high,\nand there is some space available,"},{"time":512283,"text":"two or three rooms are made\nunder the water tower,"},{"time":515159,"text":"which are used by the village for \ndifferent committee meetings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519801,"text":"We have had clear evidence\nof the great impact of this program."},{"time":526675,"text":"Before we started, there were, as usual,"},{"time":530428,"text":"more than 80 percent of people suffering\nfrom waterborne diseases."},{"time":535858,"text":"But after this, we have empirical evidence\nthat 82 percent, on average,"},{"time":542231,"text":"among all these villages --\n1,200 villages have completed it --"},{"time":546686,"text":"waterborne diseases \nhave come down 82 percent."},{"time":551823,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":558073,"text":"Women usually used to spend, \nespecially in the summer months,"},{"time":563544,"text":"about six to seven hours \na day carrying water."},{"time":571206,"text":"And when they went to carry water,"},{"time":574890,"text":"because, as I said earlier,\nit's only women who carry water,"},{"time":580259,"text":"they used to take their little children,\ngirl children, also to carry water,"},{"time":586834,"text":"or else to be back at home\nto look after the siblings."},{"time":591615,"text":"So there were less than nine percent\nof girl children attending school,"},{"time":595856,"text":"even if there was a school."},{"time":598207,"text":"And boys, about 30 percent."},{"time":601179,"text":"But girls, it has gone to about 90 percent\nand boys, almost to 100 percent."},{"time":608148,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":612795,"text":"The most vulnerable section in a village"},{"time":616027,"text":"are the landless laborers who are\nthe daily wage-earners."},{"time":620086,"text":"Because they have gone \nthrough this training"},{"time":622696,"text":"to be masons and plumbers and bar benders,"},{"time":626296,"text":"now their ability to earn has \nincreased 300 to 400 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634325,"text":"So this is a democracy in action"},{"time":637765,"text":"because there is a general body, \na governing board, the committee."},{"time":641591,"text":"People are questioning, \npeople are governing themselves,"},{"time":644461,"text":"people are learning to manage\ntheir own affairs,"},{"time":647110,"text":"they are taking their own futures\ninto their hands."},{"time":650882,"text":"And that is democracy at\nthe grassroots level in action."},{"time":658831,"text":"More than 1,200 villages \nhave so far done this."},{"time":665035,"text":"It benefits over 400,000 people\nand it's still going on."},{"time":670614,"text":"And I hope it continues to move ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677245,"text":"For India and such developing countries,"},{"time":682052,"text":"armies and armaments,"},{"time":687684,"text":"software companies and spaceships"},{"time":696486,"text":"may not be as important\nas taps and toilets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702944,"text":"Thank you. Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705375,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":709897,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}